    <title>Error when opening URLs that don’t finish with ‘/‘</title>
    <link>https://community.frontity.org/t/error-when-opening-urls-that-don-t-finish-with/4184</link>
    <description>Hi Everyone,

I have found a possible bug in Frontity. I notice this bug in my project and to know if I was doing it wrong I have reviewed your demos and I have found the same problem.

I am using Mars theme but it also happens in Twenty Twenty

The problem occurs when you use an url that doesn’t finish with &quot;/&quot;

For example in the Frontity demo (https://twentytwenty.frontity.org)

**Good Url** → https://twentytwenty.frontity.org/tag/japan/

`  https://twentytwenty.frontity.org/tag/japan/`

![image2.png|602x317](upload://qrnpsjH2X92nHdfQRi4Y1hTSnd4.png)

All information is displayed correctly

**Bad url** → https://twentytwenty.frontity.org/tag/japan

`https://twentytwenty.frontity.org/tag/japan`

![image1.png|550x270](upload://1wTyCuSe74IiDmk3MEk3NfLDhjj.png)

It shows this errors:

* **Image doesn’t load.**

* **We have this error in console.**

![image3.png|553x221](upload://tjFQ3qARZNk8cGRlzGY7DGwq1IK.png)

* **In our project we have been able to appreciate that any javascript that has to be executed on the client is not done. No delayed [Console.log](http://console.log/), useEffect or lazy javascript is working.**

**Someone else has been able to see if they have the same error or have found some solution or
workaround?**

**Thanks in advance! And good job with Frontity, we are loving it :)**</description>
